Aβ1-42 (DAEFRHDSGYEVHHQKLVFFAEDVGSNKGAIIGLMVGGV-
VIA) was prepared by solid-phase peptide synthesis (SPPS) on a 433A
Syro I synthesizer (Applied Biosystems, Foster City, CA, USA) using
Fmoc-protected L-amino acid derivatives, NovaSyn-TGA resin.


Aβ1-42 was dissolved in 10 mM NaOH, H2O and PBS (1:1:2) and added to the
cocoa extracts (62.5 μg/mL) and the L1 cocoa fractions A, B, C and D
(50 μg/mL) before treatment of the SH-SY5Y cells, to the final con-
centration of 10 μM for Aβ1-42 in the well.
